com.azure.data.cosmos.internal.changefeed

Interface LeaseStore

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    LeaseStoreManager

    public interface LeaseStore
    Represents the lease store container to deal with initialization/cleanup of leases for particular monitoring collection and lease container prefix.

    • Method Detail

      • isInitialized

        reactor.core.publisher.Mono<Boolean> isInitialized()
        Returns:
        true if the lease store is initialized.

      • markInitialized

        reactor.core.publisher.Mono<Boolean> markInitialized()
        Mark the store as initialized.
        Returns:
        a deferred computation of this operation call.

      • acquireInitializationLock

        reactor.core.publisher.Mono<Boolean> acquireInitializationLock(Duration lockExpirationTime)
        Places a lock on the lease store for initialization. Only one process may own the store for the lock time.
        Parameters:
        lockExpirationTime - the time for the lock to expire.
        Returns:
        true if the lock was acquired, false otherwise.

      • releaseInitializationLock

        reactor.core.publisher.Mono<Boolean> releaseInitializationLock()
        Releases the lock one the lease store for initialization.
        Returns:
        true if the lock was acquired and was released, false if the lock was not acquired.
